Class_Skill_Desc_Ambitious Lure: Attracts fish with large jaws and increases your chances of landing one. Occasionally guarantees you will land a large-jawed fish.</br>Can be used up to 3 times while fishing, each use increasing the effectiveness and GP cost.</br>May also attract rare species of fish. Effective on fish caught using Powerful Hookset.</br>First Use: 10 GP</br>Second Use: 20 GP</br>Third Use: 30 GP
Class_Skill_Desc_Bait: Selects the bait to apply to your line.
Class_Skill_Desc_Baited Breath: Holds your breath and reduces the wariness of nearby fish.</br>Cannot be executed when wariness exceeds a certain threshold.
Class_Skill_Desc_Big-game Fishing: Increases the chance the next large-sized fish caught will be an especially large specimen.</br>Chance of landing an especially large specimen increases based on your perception rating.</br>Angler's Art Cost: 2</br>Cancels current mooching opportunity.
Class_Skill_Desc_Cast: Casts your line and begins fishing.
Class_Skill_Desc_Cast Light: Lights up the tip of your fishing rod.
Class_Skill_Desc_Chum: Reduces the amount of time for the next fish to bite.</br>Cancels current mooching opportunity.
Class_Skill_Desc_Collect: Readies the catch to retain as a collectable.
Class_Skill_Desc_Double Hook: Hooks two or more fish in a single cast. Yield is determined by fish type and your gathering rating. Some fish cannot be double hooked.
Class_Skill_Desc_Electric Current: Electrifies the water and captures all fish present in your field of vision.</br>Wariness of other nearby fish increases with the number of fish caught.</br>Requires a catch counter of 10 to execute. Can only be executed once per spearfishing attempt.
Class_Skill_Desc_Fathom: Surveys the seas to locate teeming waters. Activates automatically when class is changed to fisher.
Class_Skill_Desc_Fish Eyes: Opens your five senses to the surrounding environment, detecting fish in a given body of water without regard for their normal hours of activity.</br>Has no effect on certain fish.</br>Duration: 60s</br>Cancels current mooching opportunity.
Class_Skill_Desc_Gig: Attempts to catch a fish using your gig, increasing the wariness of others nearby.</br>Catching more fish in a single attempt results in a smaller increase to wariness.
Class_Skill_Desc_Hook: Attempts to hook the fish nibbling on the bait.
Class_Skill_Desc_Identical Cast: Ensures you hook the same fish you previously caught. Has no effect on some fish.</br>Duration: 15s</br>Effect ends after hooking a fish, and cannot be used for consecutive casts. Cancels current mooching opportunity.</br>Effect is canceled if the same fish cannot be caught at your current fishing location.</br>Overwrites the effect of Surface Slap upon execution.</br>Cannot be executed when swimbait obtained via Spareful Hand is your selected bait.
Class_Skill_Desc_Makeshift Bait: Allows the execution of Mooch or Spareful Hand even with average-sized fish.</br>Duration: 145s</br>Angler's Art Cost: 5</br>Action has no effect on fish caught prior to execution.
Class_Skill_Desc_Modest Lure: Attracts fish with weak jaws and increases your chances of landing one. Occasionally guarantees you will land a weak-jawed fish.</br>Can be used up to 3 times while fishing, each use increasing the effectiveness and GP cost.</br>May also attract rare species of fish. Effective on fish caught using Precision Hookset.</br>First Use: 10 GP</br>Second Use: 20 GP</br>Third Use: 30 GP
Class_Skill_Desc_Mooch: Uses certain large-sized fish already hooked to your line to attract even greater prey.
Class_Skill_Desc_Mooch II: Uses certain hooked fish of average size to attract even larger prey.</br>Duration: 15s
Class_Skill_Desc_Nature's Bounty: Increases the chance of landing a large-sized fish on your next spearfishing attempt.</br>Chance of landing a large catch increases based on your perception rating.
Class_Skill_Desc_Patience: Increases the chance of landing a large-sized fish by 50% while reducing Hook efficiency by 40%.</br>Duration: 60s</br>Cancels current mooching opportunity.
Class_Skill_Desc_Patience II: Increases the chance of landing a large-sized fish by 80% while reducing Hook efficiency by 75%. Also increases the likelihood of catching an average-sized fish of greater length.</br>Duration: 145s</br>Cancels current mooching opportunity.
Class_Skill_Desc_Powerful Hookset: Negates the Inefficient Hooking status. Has no effect on certain fish with a weak bite.
Class_Skill_Desc_Precision Hookset: Negates the Inefficient Hooking status. Has no effect on certain fish with a strong bite.
Class_Skill_Desc_Prize Catch: Guarantees the next catch will be a large-sized fish.</br>Effect ends after hooking a fish. Cancels current mooching opportunity.
Class_Skill_Desc_Quit: Abandons fishing and stows your equipment.</br>※Effects active only when fishing will expire.
Class_Skill_Desc_Release: Unhooks a fish (including all those of the same type subsequently caught at your current location) and releases it back into the wild.</br>Has no effect on fish that have yet to be logged in the Fish Guide.
Class_Skill_Desc_Release List: Selects fish to be automatically released upon catching them at a given fishing hole.</br>Settings are reset upon putting away rod.</br>Has no effect on fish that have yet to be logged in the Fish Guide.
Class_Skill_Desc_Rest: Abandons fishing but keeps your equipment at the ready.
Class_Skill_Desc_Salvage: Occasionally discovers treasure maps while spearfishing.
Class_Skill_Desc_Shark Eye: Surveys the seas to locate the nearest teeming waters within skill range. Can only be executed while Fathom is active.</br>Duration: 15s
Class_Skill_Desc_Shark Eye II: Surveys the landscape to locate the highest-level teeming waters within skill range. Can only be executed while Fathom is active.</br>Duration: 15s
Class_Skill_Desc_Snagging: Adds extra hooks to the line, making it possible to land normally uncatchable fish and items.
Class_Skill_Desc_Sneak: Tread quietly, enabling you to avoid enemies up to four levels above your own.
Class_Skill_Desc_Spareful Hand: Stores certain large-sized fish as swimbait for later use.</br>Swimbait may be selected for use as bait so long as you remain at your present fishing spot.</br>Swimbait may be used even after actions that cancel mooching opportunity.</br>Cannot be executed while under the effect of Surface Slap or Identical Cast.
Class_Skill_Desc_Surface Slap: Prevents hooking the same fish you just caught. Has no effect on some fish.</br>Duration: 15s</br>Effect ends after hooking a fish. Cancels current mooching opportunity.</br>Overwrites the effect of Identical Cast upon execution.</br>Cannot be executed when swimbait obtained via Spareful Hand is your selected bait.
Class_Skill_Desc_Triple Hook: Hooks three or more fish in a single cast. Yield is determined by fish type and your gathering rating. Some fish cannot be triple hooked.
Class_Skill_Desc_Truth of Oceans: Further surveys the seas to uncover the nearest swimming shadows within skill range.
Class_Skill_Desc_Veteran Trade: Prevents the same fish you just caught from appearing again. Has no effect on some fish.
Class_Skill_Desc_Vital Sight: Sharpens your vision, making fish easier to target.</br>Angler's Art Cost: 2</br>Effect ends when you finish spearfishing at your present location.
Class_Trait_Desc_Aetherfishing: Allows you to cast your line into aetherochemical pools.
Class_Trait_Desc_Angler's Art: May grant a stack of Angler's Art upon landing a large-sized fish.</br>Maximum Stacks: 10</br>Chance of being granted Angler's Art differs between fishing and spearfishing.
Class_Trait_Desc_Auto Fathom: Automatically activates Fathom upon changing your class to fisher.
Class_Trait_Desc_Auto Sneak: Automatically activates Sneak upon changing your class to fisher. Effect is also automatically activated upon changing areas.</br>Sneak will not be automatically activated in areas where the action cannot be used.
Class_Trait_Desc_Cloudfishing: Allows you to cast your line from floating islands.
Class_Trait_Desc_Double Mooching: Allows you to mooch with a mooched fish.
Class_Trait_Desc_Dunefishing: Allows you to cast your fishing line into the desert sands.
Class_Trait_Desc_Enhanced GP Regeneratio: Raises base GP regeneration rate by one.
Raises base GP regeneration rate by a total of two.
Raises base GP regeneration rate by a total of three.
Class_Trait_Desc_Fisher's Instinct: While under the effect of Fisher's Intuition or Spearfisher's Intuition, resets the effect duration when catching certain fish.</br>Chance to trigger this effect differs between fish.
Class_Trait_Desc_Gulleye: Allows you to discern the location of fishing holes at or below your level.
Class_Trait_Desc_Hellfishing: Allows you to cast your line into magma.
Class_Trait_Desc_One with the Ocean: Automatically activates Truth of Oceans upon changing your class to fisher.
Class_Trait_Desc_Saltfishing: Allows you to cast your line into salt lakes.
Class_Trait_Desc_Skyfishing: Allows you to cast your line into the clouds.
Class_Trait_Desc_Starfishing: Allows you to cast your line in space.
